</p></entry><entry colname="col2" align="left" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Remove the 4 nuts and remove the assembly by pulling it towards you. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The drive motor is in the rear of the assembly. Do not damage the motor. 
